00:56:01,191 --> 00:56:05,691
Now, you really are
one hard man to...

996
00:56:07,364 --> 00:56:09,157
Purify

997
00:56:20,794 --> 00:56:23,713
ah, senator,
and what can I do for--

998
00:56:26,717 --> 00:56:29,177
oh, hello, Billy.
Come on in.

999
00:56:31,972 --> 00:56:35,475
Well, did you have
your talk with Bailey?

1000
00:56:35,475 --> 00:56:37,810
I had my talk
with Mr. Bailey.

1001
00:56:37,811 --> 00:56:40,522
He told me that he's been
telling you what to do

1002
00:56:40,522 --> 00:56:42,440
for the past 30 years.

1003
00:56:44,234 --> 00:56:47,320
I called him a liar.

1004
00:56:47,321 --> 00:56:51,821
Listen, son, come on over here
and sit down, will you?

1005
00:56:52,242 --> 00:56:56,742
I'm sorry. I don't feel very
much like sitting down, sir.

1006
00:56:57,122 --> 00:57:01,084
Oh, lord,
i know how you feel.

1007
00:57:01,084 --> 00:57:04,712
I was hoping you'd be
spared all this.

1008
00:57:04,713 --> 00:57:07,924
You've been living
in a dream world, Billy.

1009
00:57:07,925 --> 00:57:10,636
The idealist sees everything
as black and white,

1010
00:57:10,636 --> 00:57:12,137
angel and devil,

1011
00:57:12,137 --> 00:57:14,347
but that isn't how it goes
in the real world.

1012
00:57:14,348 --> 00:57:17,601
It's cruel, brutal, unfair.

1013
00:57:17,601 --> 00:57:19,477
You don't belong here, Billy.

1014
00:57:19,478 --> 00:57:21,771
Forget Bailey
and what he said.

1015
00:57:21,772 --> 00:57:24,107
Forget you ever heard of
the willett creek reactor.

1016
00:57:24,107 --> 00:57:26,317
That doesn't
answer my question.

1017
00:57:26,318 --> 00:57:28,778
Does Bailey
tell you how to vote?

1018
00:57:28,779 --> 00:57:33,279
Now, listen, Billy.
Please try to understand.

1019
00:57:33,450 --> 00:57:37,078
I know it's tough to run head-on
into the world of facts,

1020
00:57:37,079 --> 00:57:40,457
but it's a question
of give and take.

1021
00:57:40,457 --> 00:57:42,667
You've got to play
by these rules.

1022
00:57:42,668 --> 00:57:44,378
You've got to compromise.

1023
00:57:44,378 --> 00:57:47,422
If one must shut his eyes
that a reactor has to be built,

1024
00:57:47,422 --> 00:57:49,173
it's a small compromise.

1025
00:57:49,174 --> 00:57:53,094
The best men ever to serve in
this senate had to make deals.

1026
00:57:53,095 --> 00:57:55,138
You understand that?

1027
00:57:55,138 --> 00:57:59,308
Your Thomas Jefferson
had to make one on slavery,

1028
00:57:59,309 --> 00:58:01,227
or the declaration
of independence

1029
00:58:01,228 --> 00:58:03,480
would have never have gone
out of committee.

1030
00:58:03,480 --> 00:58:07,358
Now, believe me,
i know how you feel.

1031
00:58:07,359 --> 00:58:11,859
30 years ago,
i had those ideals too.

1032
00:58:12,072 --> 00:58:13,490
I was you!

1033
00:58:13,490 --> 00:58:15,617
I had to make the decision
you're being asked to make

1034
00:58:15,617 --> 00:58:16,909
today, and I made it.

1035
00:58:16,910 --> 00:58:19,162
I compromised.

1036
00:58:19,162 --> 00:58:21,247
Yes, I compromised,

1037
00:58:21,248 --> 00:58:24,251
so that all these years
i could sit in the senate

1038
00:58:24,251 --> 00:58:27,671
and serve the people
in a thousand beneficial ways.

1039
00:58:27,671 --> 00:58:30,757
You have to make alliances
with organizations

1040
00:58:30,757 --> 00:58:32,717
like Bailey's and
the big corporations.

1041
00:58:32,718 --> 00:58:35,429
You have to play ball,
or you can't survive.

1042
00:58:35,429 --> 00:58:37,848
You can't count
on the people voting.

1043
00:58:37,848 --> 00:58:40,350
You know how many people
voted in my last election?

1044
00:58:40,350 --> 00:58:43,186
Less than 22%
of the registered voters.

1045
00:58:43,186 --> 00:58:45,521
All I had to do was get 11%,

1046
00:58:45,522 --> 00:58:49,359
and Bailey's machine can
turn that out every time.

1047
00:58:49,359 --> 00:58:51,819
I know you're not going
to decide as I did.

1048
00:58:51,820 --> 00:58:53,488
I can see that in your eyes.

1049
00:58:54,740 --> 00:58:57,200
But I told you all this
because...

1050
00:58:59,703 --> 00:59:03,248
I've grown very fond of you--
like a son, in fact--

1051
00:59:03,248 --> 00:59:06,084
and I don't want
to see you get hurt.

1052
00:59:06,084 --> 00:59:09,712
The powers here,
and the baileys,

1053
00:59:09,713 --> 00:59:12,757
they're ruthless, Billy.

1054
00:59:12,758 --> 00:59:16,136
I think you're beginning
to see some of that.

1055
00:59:18,055 --> 00:59:20,182
You've already gone too far.

1056
00:59:22,601 --> 00:59:24,436
You're no longer safe here.

1057
00:59:26,855 --> 00:59:29,899
When that deficiency bill
comes up in senate tomorrow,

1058
00:59:29,900 --> 00:59:31,192
stay away.

1059
00:59:31,193 --> 00:59:34,696
Just stay away.
It's that simple.

1060
00:59:35,781 --> 00:59:37,032
Please.

1061
00:59:38,909 --> 00:59:40,535
Just stay away.

1062
00:59:55,509 --> 00:59:57,385
And under previous orders,

1063
00:59:57,385 --> 00:59:59,261
the senate
resumes consideration

1064
00:59:59,262 --> 01:00:00,930
of yesterday's unfinished
business,

1065
01:00:00,931 --> 01:00:02,349
which the clerk will read.

1066
01:00:02,349 --> 01:00:06,849
A bill, hr7700, providing
for deficiency appropriations

1067
01:00:07,187 --> 01:00:11,191
for the fiscal year 1977,
and for other purposes.

1068
01:00:11,191 --> 01:00:12,692
The bill is open
to amendments.

1069
01:00:12,692 --> 01:00:15,069
- Mr. president.
- Senator Jack.

1070
01:00:15,070 --> 01:00:16,571
Mr. president,
i wish to address myself

1071
01:00:16,571 --> 01:00:20,074
to section 40 of the bill.

1072
01:00:20,075 --> 01:00:22,577
I want specifically to talk
about the nuclear plant

1073
01:00:22,577 --> 01:00:25,246
- on willett creek.
- Mr. president!

1074
01:00:25,247 --> 01:00:26,831
Will the senator yield?

1075
01:00:29,835 --> 01:00:31,586
Yes, yes, sir.

1076
01:00:31,586 --> 01:00:35,506
Mr. president, I have
risen to a difficult task

1077
01:00:35,507 --> 01:00:39,886
to say that out of evidence
that has come to my attention,

1078
01:00:39,886 --> 01:00:44,181
I consider senator Jack
unworthy to address this body.

1079
01:00:52,023 --> 01:00:53,482
Order in the senate!

1080
01:00:55,360 --> 01:00:58,905
The chair will clear the gallery
unless order is restored.

1081
01:00:58,905 --> 01:01:01,532
- What in the hell is going on?
- I don't know.

1082
01:01:01,533 --> 01:01:04,285
Payne's jumping Billy Jack
about something.

1083
01:01:04,286 --> 01:01:05,662
Proceed, sir.

1084
01:01:05,662 --> 01:01:09,624
I have hesitated to speak,
but in all conscience I must.

1085
01:01:09,624 --> 01:01:13,794
It is a charge as grave
as has ever been made

1086
01:01:13,795 --> 01:01:16,839
from this floor
against a fellow member.

1087
01:01:16,840 --> 01:01:20,260
I refer to the bill he has
presented in this chamber,

1088
01:01:20,260 --> 01:01:23,137
providing for his
national youth camp.

1089
01:01:23,138 --> 01:01:26,266
Senators,

1090
01:01:26,266 --> 01:01:30,766
I have conclusive
evidence to prove

1091
01:01:31,062 --> 01:01:34,315
that my colleague
owns the very land

1092
01:01:34,316 --> 01:01:36,234
described in his bill.

1093
01:01:40,322 --> 01:01:43,867
He bought it the day following
his appointment to the senate,

1094
01:01:43,867 --> 01:01:47,954
and he is holding it,
using this body

1095
01:01:47,954 --> 01:01:52,454
and his privileged position
for his own personal profit.

1096
01:01:52,959 --> 01:01:55,836
- Tonto had a racket?
- It doesn't make sense!

1097
01:01:55,837 --> 01:02:00,337
Accordingly,
i offer a resolution

1098
01:02:01,134 --> 01:02:04,554
for an immediate inquiry
by the select committee

1099
01:02:04,554 --> 01:02:09,054
on standards and conduct as
to the fitness of my colleague

1100
01:02:10,435 --> 01:02:13,354
to continue to sit
in this chamber.

1101
01:02:26,660 --> 01:02:30,330
Order, the committee calls
governor hopper, please.

1102
01:02:30,330 --> 01:02:32,498
Governor hopper.

1103
01:02:32,499 --> 01:02:33,416
Governor,

1104
01:02:33,416 --> 01:02:37,503
were you there the morning that
Mr. Allen was present?

1105
01:02:37,504 --> 01:02:40,048
Ah, yes Mr. chairman,
i was present the morning

1106
01:02:40,048 --> 01:02:42,341
that Kenneth Allen
came to the state capital,

1107
01:02:42,342 --> 01:02:46,679
bringing proof that Billy Jack
had a deed to that campsite.

1108
01:02:46,680 --> 01:02:49,516
I, uh, frankly was
in a state of shock.

1109
01:02:49,516 --> 01:02:51,184
I mean, Billy Jack
of all people.

1110
01:02:51,184 --> 01:02:53,561
He is a hero to people
all over my state.

1111
01:02:53,561 --> 01:02:56,021
Now, governor, what did you do

1112
01:02:56,022 --> 01:02:58,357
when Mr. Allen brought this
to your attention?

1113
01:02:58,358 --> 01:03:00,943
Ah, I had a consultation with
the head of the department

1114
01:03:00,944 --> 01:03:03,696
of records, Mr. Arthur Kim.

1115
01:03:03,697 --> 01:03:07,575
Mr. Kim, do you remember
recording this deed?

1116
01:03:07,575 --> 01:03:10,411
Yes.

1117
01:03:10,412 --> 01:03:13,081
On the date set forth here?

1118
01:03:13,081 --> 01:03:16,292
Mr. Kenneth Allen came
before me to record this deed,

1119
01:03:16,293 --> 01:03:20,255
setting over these 400 acres
in the name of Billy Jack.

1120
01:03:22,882 --> 01:03:25,050
Order, please.

1121
01:03:25,051 --> 01:03:28,721
How long have you known
senator Jack, Mr. Allen?

1122
01:03:28,722 --> 01:03:30,724
Oh, many, many years.

1123
01:03:30,724 --> 01:03:33,393
He often camped
around willett creek.

1124
01:03:33,393 --> 01:03:37,063
Now, a lot of people were afraid
of Billy Jack, but I liked him.

1125
01:03:37,063 --> 01:03:39,148
And then when he came to me
with this proposition--

1126
01:03:39,149 --> 01:03:42,110
what proposition,
please, Mr. Allen?

1127
01:03:42,110 --> 01:03:45,571
Well, he said he had a chance
to sell that leased land

1128
01:03:45,572 --> 01:03:48,157
for at least five thousand
dollars an acre.

1129
01:03:48,158 --> 01:03:51,077
Me, I was happy to get
five hundred dollars an acre.

1130
01:03:51,077 --> 01:03:55,247
So, we set it up like this:
I deeded him the land,

1131
01:03:55,248 --> 01:03:57,917
and he gave me a contract
guaranteeing me

1132
01:03:57,917 --> 01:04:01,629
half of what he got
if he made the sale.

1133
01:04:01,629 --> 01:04:04,465
Well, in a way, it sounded
kind of fishy at the time,

1134
01:04:04,466 --> 01:04:08,052
but that's the way most
of these developers work.

1135
01:04:08,053 --> 01:04:10,138
So it wasn't until he sent me
this telegram

1136
01:04:10,138 --> 01:04:13,266
that I realized there was some
really dirty business going on.

1137
01:04:13,266 --> 01:04:15,268
May we see the telegram,
please?

1138
01:04:15,268 --> 01:04:17,270
- Yes.
- Thank you.

1139
01:04:20,648 --> 01:04:23,859
"Urgent.
Camp bill introduced.

1140
01:04:23,860 --> 01:04:25,862
"Senator Payne will help.

1141
01:04:25,862 --> 01:04:27,738
"You have a deal on that land.

1142
01:04:27,739 --> 01:04:29,657
"Contracts to follow.

1143
01:04:29,657 --> 01:04:30,991
Billy Jack."

1144
01:04:32,911 --> 01:04:35,163
Order, please.

1145
01:04:35,163 --> 01:04:39,000
That contract you mentioned,
have you got that document?

1146
01:04:39,000 --> 01:04:41,836
That land wouldn't be in his
name if I didn't, yes, sir.

1147
01:04:41,836 --> 01:04:43,587
Signed, sealed,
and delivered.

1148
01:04:46,674 --> 01:04:48,842
Order, please.

1149
01:04:48,843 --> 01:04:51,720
After a long study
of this signature,

1150
01:04:51,721 --> 01:04:55,683
it is my professional opinion
that it definitely is

1151
01:04:55,683 --> 01:04:57,810
Billy Jack's
own handwriting.

1152
01:05:01,773 --> 01:05:04,942
Therefore, it is my opinion
as a professional,

1153
01:05:04,943 --> 01:05:08,488
and as an expert
on handwriting,

1154
01:05:08,488 --> 01:05:11,324
that the signature
of Billy Jack

1155
01:05:11,324 --> 01:05:14,952
on this contract
is a forgery.

1156
01:05:20,458 --> 01:05:24,958
It is difficult to tell the real
thing and a clever forgery,

1157
01:05:25,171 --> 01:05:27,840
and you'll get differing
opinions from experts,

1158
01:05:27,841 --> 01:05:31,511
but I'd be willing to stake
my 40 years in this profession

1159
01:05:31,511 --> 01:05:34,055
on the fact that this
is not a forgery

1160
01:05:34,055 --> 01:05:37,975
and is the actual signature
of Billy Jack.

1161
01:05:42,772 --> 01:05:46,275
Mr. chairman, gentlemen...

1162
01:05:49,154 --> 01:05:53,654
This is an excruciatingly
painful duty for me.

1163
01:05:56,911 --> 01:05:59,830
This young boy

1164
01:05:59,831 --> 01:06:02,750
is the nephew
of my very dearest friend.

1165
01:06:04,961 --> 01:06:08,839
I sponsored him
in the senate.

1166
01:06:08,840 --> 01:06:13,340
I helped him
frame his camp bill.

1167
01:06:13,678 --> 01:06:17,765
And when he presented it
to the senate,

1168
01:06:17,765 --> 01:06:21,977
I went over
to congratulate him,

1169
01:06:21,978 --> 01:06:25,606
but I pointed out
to him that

1170
01:06:25,607 --> 01:06:30,107
a nuclear plant was going up
on the very site

1171
01:06:30,111 --> 01:06:33,447
he had selected for his camp.

1172
01:06:33,448 --> 01:06:37,948
I said there are hundreds of
equally good campsites nearby.

1173
01:06:39,329 --> 01:06:42,206
I suggested that he

1174
01:06:42,207 --> 01:06:46,628
choose another site
for his camp.

1175
01:06:46,628 --> 01:06:49,464
He got furious.

1176
01:06:49,464 --> 01:06:52,467
He said "move the plant."

1177
01:06:52,467 --> 01:06:54,886
I had heard about
his violent temper,

1178
01:06:54,886 --> 01:06:59,386
but I was amazed
at his reaction.

1179
01:06:59,974 --> 01:07:02,476
He began to argue with me.

1180
01:07:02,477 --> 01:07:06,977
He said that "unless
i get that very same site,

1181
01:07:07,649 --> 01:07:09,901
"i will attack
the willett creek plant.

1182
01:07:09,901 --> 01:07:14,401
I'll charge graft,
political motives."

1183
01:07:16,824 --> 01:07:21,324
He would use anything he could
think of to defeat it.

1184
01:07:22,705 --> 01:07:25,999
Well, faced with that,
gentlemen...

1185
01:07:28,086 --> 01:07:32,586
In spite of my very deep
personal feelings for the boy...

1186
01:07:35,134 --> 01:07:37,177
My sense of duty...

1187
01:07:38,346 --> 01:07:42,846
Required that his expulsion
from the senate

1188
01:07:43,726 --> 01:07:46,145
would be the only
acceptable solution.

1189
01:07:54,654 --> 01:07:56,822
Senator Jack, please.

1190
01:08:08,459 --> 01:08:11,462
The committee is ready for your
testimony now, senator Jack.

1191
01:08:37,322 --> 01:08:41,534
Order!
Order in this courtroom!

1192
01:08:41,534 --> 01:08:44,245
That's it.
He's drawn and quartered.

1193
01:08:44,245 --> 01:08:46,830
You know, I didn't think
he was guilty until this moment.

1194
01:08:59,510 --> 01:09:02,930
We'll get the whole thing
over all the front pages.

1195
01:09:02,930 --> 01:09:06,224
Yeah, we'll be sending some
photos for the TV coverage.

1196
01:09:06,225 --> 01:09:09,561
Listen, make sure you give Joe
Payne a big buildup, will ya?

1197
01:09:09,562 --> 01:09:13,732
Yeah, sort of an "Abraham
sacrificing his son

1198
01:09:13,733 --> 01:09:16,068
for the good of the people"
sort of thing.

1199
01:09:16,069 --> 01:09:19,906
Yeah, sure, they're having
a hell of a time.

1200
01:10:00,947 --> 01:10:02,907
You'll never guess
who I found.

1201
01:10:05,827 --> 01:10:07,078
Saunders.

1202
01:10:08,329 --> 01:10:11,040
And guess what she found
in her safety deposit box.

1203
01:10:13,668 --> 01:10:16,462
All of foley's
classified material.

1204
01:10:19,674 --> 01:10:23,427
She's willing to come back and
make a fight of it if you are.

1205
01:10:23,428 --> 01:10:26,013
To make a fight of what?

1206
01:10:26,013 --> 01:10:28,765
- You mean you're gonna quit?
- Who's the enemy?

1207
01:10:28,766 --> 01:10:32,102
I don't even know who
I'm supposed to be fighting.

1208
01:10:32,103 --> 01:10:34,730
Look, Billy, who better
than you knows that

1209
01:10:34,731 --> 01:10:37,734
you can't reform congress
from within?

1210
01:10:37,734 --> 01:10:40,194
So why don't you use
the filibuster

1211
01:10:40,194 --> 01:10:41,445
as a way to teach people

1212
01:10:41,446 --> 01:10:45,946
how they can get
a national referendum?

1213
01:10:46,868 --> 01:10:49,579
Even if you lose,
who cares?

1214
01:10:49,579 --> 01:10:50,746
You'll have taught people

1215
01:10:50,747 --> 01:10:52,665
how to get around
a corrupt congress.

1216
01:10:56,961 --> 01:11:01,215
Your quitting is sure gonna
shatter a lot of hopes, though.

1217
01:11:01,215 --> 01:11:04,593
Well, I'm sorry about that.

1218
01:11:04,594 --> 01:11:06,804
But this is different.
Lt's-- lt's--

1219
01:11:08,389 --> 01:11:10,057
it's just too sophisticated.

1220
01:11:13,227 --> 01:11:15,812
Maybe you're right.

1221
01:11:15,813 --> 01:11:18,732
Maybe if the only solution
you have to crucial problems

1222
01:11:18,733 --> 01:11:23,233
is to take off your boots
and kick people in the head,

1223
01:11:23,404 --> 01:11:25,531
maybe you
just should go home.

1224
01:11:41,589 --> 01:11:46,089
"L have sworn
upon the altar of god

1225
01:11:46,928 --> 01:11:51,098
"eternal hostility

1226
01:11:51,098 --> 01:11:55,598
"against every form
of tyranny

1227
01:11:56,521 --> 01:11:59,148
over the mind of man."

1228
01:13:18,227 --> 01:13:22,064
<i>That we here,
highly resolve</i>

1229
01:13:22,064 --> 01:13:25,567
<i>that this nation shall,
under god,</i>

1230
01:13:25,568 --> 01:13:28,654
<i>have a new birth of freedom.</i>

1231
01:13:28,654 --> 01:13:30,989
<i>And that government
of the people,</i>

1232
01:13:30,990 --> 01:13:34,994
<i>by the people,
and for the people</i>

1233
01:13:34,994 --> 01:13:37,746
<i>shall not perish
from the earth.</i>

